refrain /rɪˈfreɪn/

(refraining,refrained,refrains) 

1. V-I If you refrain from doing something, you deliberately do not do it. 忍住; 克制 

例： Mrs. Hardie refrained from making any comment. 哈迪太太忍住了没做任何评论。 

2. N-COUNT A refrain is a short, simple part of a song, which is repeated many times. 副歌 

例： ...a refrain from an old song. …一首老歌的副歌。 

3. N-COUNT A refrain is a comment or saying that people often repeat. 一再重复的话 

例： Rosa's constant refrain is that she doesn't have a life. 罗莎总是不断重复的一句话就是她生活得很无聊。

